Introduction to Python Project : FoodHub Data Analysis¶

Problem Statement¶

FoodHub is a food aggregator app in the New Yotk that offers access to multiple restaurants through a single smartphone app. The customers can place online orders at the restaurants and the app assigns a delivery partner from the company to pick up the order from the restaurant once it is confirmed. Once the food is packed, the delivery partner delivers the order to the customer and also the customer can track the delivery process through the app. The customers can rate the order in the app. FoodHub earns money by collecting a fixed margin on the delivery order from the restaurants.

Objective¶

FoodHub wants to analyze the customer data to get an idea about the demand of different restaurants in order to improve the customer experience. As a Data Scientist, the task is to analyse the data to find the answers to the key business questions and provide insights that can help the company improve its business.

Data Dictionary¶

  • order_id: Unique ID of the order.
  • customer_id: Id of the customer who ordered the food.
  • restaurant_name: Name of the restaurant.
  • cuisine_type: Type of the cuisine ordered by the customer.
  • cost_of_the_order: Cost of the order (in dollars).
  • day_of_the_week: Denotes if the order is placed on weekday or weekend.
  • rating: Rating given by customer out of 5.
  • food_preparation_time: Time taken by the restaurant to prepare the food (in minutes). It is calcuated by taking the difference between the restaurant's order confirmation and the delivery person's pick-up confirmation.
  • delivery_time: Time taken by the delivery person to deliver the food (in minutes). It is calcuated by taking the difference between the delivery person's pick-up confirmation and drop-off information.

Question 14: The company charges the restaurant 25% on the orders having cost greater than 20 dollars and 15% on the orders having cost greater than 5 dollars. Find the net revenue generated by the company across all orders. [3 marks]¶

In [53]:
# Write the code here
def net_revenue(cost_of_the_order):
  if cost_of_the_order > 20:
    return cost_of_the_order*0.25
  elif cost_of_the_order > 5:
    return cost_of_the_order*0.15
  else:
    return 0.0
data['revenue'] = data['cost_of_the_order'].apply(net_revenue)
net_revenue = data['revenue'].sum()
print(f'The net revenue generated by the company across all orders is {net_revenue: .2f} dollars.')

The net revenue generated by the company across all orders is  6166.30 dollars.

Observations:¶

A new column 'revenue' is created and the net revenue generated by the company across all the orders is 6166.30 dollars.

Conclusion and Recommendations¶

Question 17: What are your conclusions from the analysis? What recommendations would you like to share to help improve the business? (You can use cuisine type and feedback ratings to drive your business recommendations.) [6 marks]¶

Conclusions:¶

  • The American cuisine is the most ordered cuisine on both weekdays as well as on weekend while the least ordered cuisine on weekdays is the Korean cuisine and that on weekends is the Vietnamese cuisine.
  • The mean delivery time on weekdays is 28.34 minutes which is higher than that of the weekends which is 22.47 minutes.
  • The restaurants with the higher orders and ratings > 4 are the Blue Ribbon Fried Chicken, Blue Ribbon Sushi, Shake Shack and The Meatball Shop.
  • Most of the food preparation time is between 20 to 35 minutes.
  • For a huge number of orders (736 orders), there is no rating given while for the rated orders, most of them are rated with 4 or 5.
  • Most of the orders are of lower costs (5 to 20 dollars) and only 29.24% of the order costs above 20 dollars.

Recommendations:¶

  • Since Korean and Vietnamese cuisine are the least ordered cuisines, so promoting these cuisines with discounts, offers, combo meals or cross cuisine meal combo can help in improving the sales of these cuisine.
  • Hiring more delivery partners or limiting the delivery areas at peak hours can help in faster delivery of the orders in the weekdays.
  • The top rated restaurants can be featured on the app home screen and additional offers can be provided for these restaurants on their signature dishes in order to increase the customer trust and also to attract new customers.
  • Promotions can be made as 'guarantee for order delivery under 40 minutes' or the restaurants can offer express delivery to orders that require less food preparation time.
  • Pop-up notifications can be prompted to the users to rate their orders and also submit feedback for their orders. These rating can be given seperately for the restaurants and delivery partners.
  • For higher cost orders, free delivery offers can be introduced or some freebies or additional coupons which can be used on the next time orders can be given.
